node_modules/
dist/
*.tsbuildinfo
coverage/
# Transient state lives in $BROWX_WORKSPACE (~/.browxai/), NOT here. Guardrail
# entries below catch anything that would accidentally land in-tree.
.browxai/
.browx-profile/
.env
.env.*
# captured / managed browser session state — never commit
.auth/
.browx-profile/
*.storageState.json
# editor / OS cruft
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log

# Raw client-named adopter/agent reports — they keep dropping these in-tree,
# but the repo is heading public. They MUST be sanitized into a target-
# agnostic docs/adoption-report-*.md before anything is committed; the raw
# form is NEVER tracked. Broad on purpose: any *-REPORT-*.md / REPORT-*.md /
# *-report.md at the repo ROOT is raw-until-sanitized. Canonical reports live
# under docs/ (path-anchored rules below don't match docs/).
# (Hygiene: cf. docs/first-consumer-asks.md round-10/11/14.)
/*-REPORT-*.md
/REPORT-*.md
/*-report.md
/*-report-*.md
FIELD-REPORT-*.md
USAGE-REPORT-*.md
*-field-report.md
